<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="dress-n">dress <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /dres/    美 /dres/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] (某种款式或某种场合穿的)衣服：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>wear <strong>casual</strong> / <strong>formal dress</strong>
穿便服/礼服</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 连衣裙：</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>dressed /drest/ adj [不用于名词前]   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Dressed in</strong> a white uniform, he looks more like a cook than a doctor. 
他穿着白色的制服，看起来不像个医生，倒更像个厨师。</p></div></div>